Rhodes Inc said it now estimates fourthquarter, ended February 28, earnings were eight cts a share,down from the 25 cts earned in the final quarter of fiscal1986.    The company said the major causes for the reduction were anunfavorable LIFO adjustment and softer than projected sales inthe quarter, due primarily to unfavorable weather.    Despite the 4th qtr results, Rhodes said, "net income forthe year just ended should come close to the record level ofthe previous year" -- 1.61 dlrs dlrs a share. Reuter&#3;